				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[4. GENERAL CONSIDERATIONS FOR METABOLOMICS ANALYSIS]]></text>
			</staticText>
		</band>
		<band height="195">
			<staticText>
				<reportElement positionType="Float" x="25" y="0" width="545" height="195" uuid="b3a4cbed-c5b0-41ed-9bb5-a994d3679074"/>
				<textElement textAlignment="Justified" verticalAlignment="Middle" markup="html">
					<font size="12" pdfFontName="net/sf/jasperreports/fonts/dejavu/DejaVuSerif-Italic.ttf" isPdfEmbedded="true"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[General specimen collection and handling (including avoidance of cross contamination) see EN ISO 15189:2012, 5.2.6, 5.4.4. 
<br>
<br>Consumables and kits were verified upon use in examination see EN ISO 15189:2012,5.5.1.2 and 5.5.1.3 
<br>
<br>All steps of a diagnostic workflow, comprising the pre-analytical steps, stability, storage conditions and analytical steps, were verified and validated EN ISO 15189.
<br>
<br>Safety regulations on facilities, transport and handling shall be considered (see ENISO 1589:2012, 5.2.3. and 5.4.5., and ISO 15190]]></text>
			</staticText>
		</band>
